  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is a financial crime involving concealing the origins of illegally obtained money through a series of transactions. While specific legal definitions can vary between jurisdictions, generally it involves three key stages:\n\n1. Placement - Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering - Concealing the source through complex financial transactions\n3. Integration - Making illegally obtained money appear legitimate\n\nKey legal elements typically include:\n- Knowingly processing proceeds from criminal activity\n- Attempting to disguise the origin of illegal funds\n- Engaging in financial transactions to hide criminal proceeds\n- Transforming cash from illegal activities into seemingly legal assets\n\nSpecific definitions and penalties vary by country and jurisdiction.",
